                <head>No. 620<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Foreign Ministers of the United States, France, and the United Kingdom met in
                    London from October 16 through October 18 to discuss a proposal for a Four-Power
                    meeting with the Soviet Union. Concerning these talks, as well as bilateral
                    talks between the United States and French officials on other issues such as
                    Indochina and <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>, see the editorial note, <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1709">volume V, Part 2, page 1709</ref>.</p>
            </div>
